    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-teriyaki-tray-bake-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut your <strong>sweet potato[es]</strong> (skin on) into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Cut your <strong>red onion[s]</strong> into wedges, leaving the skin on (this helps them cook quicker!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-teriyaki-tray-bake-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped sweet potato</strong> and <strong>onion wedges</strong> to a tray (or two!) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for an initial 15-20 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-teriyaki-tray-bake-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>cornflour</strong> to a small bowl with 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Heat a pot with a lid over a medium-low heat</p><p>Add your <strong>agave</strong>, <strong>soy sauce </strong>and <strong>cornflour mixture</strong> to the pot and cook, uncovered, for 1-2 min, stirring frequently, or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 this is your <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong></p><p>Once thickened, transfer the sauce to a bowl and set aside for later</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-teriyaki-tray-bake-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim, then chop your<strong> green beans</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-teriyaki-tray-bake-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, push them<strong> </strong>to one side of the tray[s] and add the <strong>halved green beans </strong>on top \u2013 these are your <strong>roasted vegetables</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>meat-free chick'n </strong>to the other side of the tray[s] and return the tray[s] to the oven for 10-13 min or until the beans are tender and the meat-free chick'n is brown and has warmed through</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-teriyaki-tray-bake-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once everything is cooked, carefully cut off the root[s] and remove the skin from the <strong>roasted onion wedges</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-chick-n-teriyaki-tray-bake-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>roasted vegetables </strong>and <strong>meat-free chick'n </strong>over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>teriyaki sauce</strong> over everything and garnish with your <strong>toasted sesame seeds</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
